The paper deals with network design games, which are a subfield of game theory (cs.GT). The focus is on multicast games, which involve the transmission of data from a single source to multiple destinations, and thus falls under the category of network protocols and algorithms (cs.NI). The paper also involves the analysis of graphs and their properties, which is a topic in data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The techniques used in the paper involve optimization and approximation algorithms, which are relevant to the field of social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper involves the analysis of the price of stability, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT).
